Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Exercises: Distributions", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9479054070007057`*^9, 
  3.947905412857245*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6c15128d-34df-4774-80a1-\
74dd6740b767"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "1. A study on breeding birds collects information such as the length of \
their eggs (in mm). Assume that the length is normally distributed with \[Mu] \
= 42.1mm and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "608436a1-103d-43fb-ba79-bc51f583c582"],
 "= ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", "20.8", ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f24b4a4e-7af5-455b-8094-9c62ae7e999e"],
 ". What is the probability of:\n(a) finding an egg with a length greater \
than 50 mm?\n(b) finding an egg between 30 and 40 mm in length?"
}], "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947905416965939*^9, 3.947905487662099*^9}, {
   3.947905540282009*^9, 3.947905581866295*^9}, {3.947905852395067*^9, 
   3.947905862893476*^9}, {3.947905933284548*^9, 3.947905936055468*^9}, 
   3.980438757161825*^9},ExpressionUUID->"d4e99adf-9a7f-4918-a0bc-\
ccedf3c27f08"],

Cell["\<\
(a) Our random variable X is normally distributed. Hence, the probability of \
finding an egg with a length greater than 50mm is equal to:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947905952010242*^9, 3.947905966213934*^9}, {
  3.947906067709934*^9, 
  3.947906087229162*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1a6ff061-d028-415a-b325-\
afb454c8c83d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"1.", "-", 
  RowBox[{"CDF", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"NormalDistribution", "[", 
     RowBox[{"42.1", ",", "20.8"}], "]"}], ",", "50"}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947905970046673*^9, 3.947906001942883*^9}, {
  3.947906048111054*^9, 3.947906051542111*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[487]:=",ExpressionUUID->"af80f336-2df2-4681-accc-d05fd8ffd71e"],

Cell[BoxData["0.35204408592945147`"], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.947906003316165*^9, 3.947906053025671*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[487]=",ExpressionUUID->"006b7451-6b93-41b8-88e4-50e78cb346fc"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["(b) This can be calculated as follows:", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947906092585258*^9, 
  3.947906104930995*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b8dcb74a-8222-4094-89f3-\
2bc779a91ecb"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"N", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"CDF", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"NormalDistribution", "[", 
      RowBox[{"42.1", ",", "20.8"}], "]"}], ",", "40"}], "]"}], "-", 
   RowBox[{"CDF", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"NormalDistribution", "[", 
      RowBox[{"42.1", ",", "20.8"}], "]"}], ",", "30"}], "]"}]}], 
  "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947906107815209*^9, 3.947906134072801*^9}, {
  3.947906168755245*^9, 3.947906171259718*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[490]:=",ExpressionUUID->"0daa4a9a-2796-4c7f-963a-e4b56b54cb98"],

Cell[BoxData["0.17941647465731442`"], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947906135325098*^9, 3.9479061715686502`*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[490]=",ExpressionUUID->"799620e0-9cbe-4b20-aa2e-5763c543dbff"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
That means, the probability of finding an egg between 30 and 40 mm in length \
is approximately 18%.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947906205703134*^9, 
  3.947906221266758*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9448adef-7081-4569-8629-\
451430e60e7b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
2. Felix states that he is able to distinguish a freshly ground coffee blend \
from an ordinary supermarket coffee. One of his friends asks him to taste 10 \
cups of coffee and tell him which coffee he has tasted. Suppose that Felix \
has actually no clue about coffee and simply guesses the brand. What is the \
probability of at least 8 correct guesses?
\
\>", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947905579458556*^9, 
  3.9479056103875732`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3d7d2f17-b467-4af0-8bab-\
d9774be13be2"],

Cell["\<\
Each guess is a Bernoulli experiment where the right answer is given with a \
probability of 50%. The number of correct guesses therefore follows a \
binomial distribution, i . e . X \[Tilde] Binomial (10,0.5) . The probability \
of giving the right answer at least 8 times is then \
P(X=8)+P(X=9)+P(X=10)=1-P(X<=7). Hence:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947906257718916*^9, 3.9479063492889767`*^9}, 
   3.94790656315751*^9, {3.9479066742743597`*^9, 
   3.947906717233653*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9aacae74-7221-4a2f-8305-\
9e2267fc460f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"1.", "-", 
  RowBox[{"CDF", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"BinomialDistribution", "[", 
     RowBox[{"10", ",", "0.5"}], "]"}], ",", "7"}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947906567152763*^9, 3.947906567775474*^9}, {
  3.9479067276679163`*^9, 3.9479067444453707`*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[491]:=",ExpressionUUID->"790d78e4-9983-4b90-b7f6-e80547fe6ea3"],

Cell[BoxData["0.05468750000000022`"], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.947906745379237*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[491]=",ExpressionUUID->"9439dcb1-b2af-4496-a602-f873846f5f26"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
Hence, the probability that Felix guess correctly at least 8 times is \
approximately equal to 5.47%.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.947906759257056*^9, 
  3.9479068031470823`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ef36bfc0-d50d-4cca-93c9-\
f8d4e20cb95e"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
